CSS from A to Z Learn how to style your pages
content:
CSS from A to Z Learn how to style your pages
CSS is a way to make web pages look good . It stands for Cascading Style Sheets . Think of HTML as building the house, and CSS as painting the walls and picking out furniture . HTML puts the words and pictures on the page . CSS changes the colors, fonts, and how things are arranged .

CSS is one of the three main parts of a webpage . HTML gives the page structure . JavaScript makes it interactive . And CSS makes it look nice . CSS lets you change the font, color, size, and spacing of things on your page . You can even use it to add animations .

for more:https://short-jambo.ink/VEAZTlyj

local dim_x = 5 
local dim_y = 4


for mx = -1, dim_x + 1 do
	turtle.turnLeft() 
	for my = 0, dim_y do
		turtle.up()
		local has_block, data = turtle.inspect()
		if has_block then
			print(data.name)
			if string.find(data.name, "cobblemon") then
				print("picking " + data.name)
				turtle.place()
			end
		else
		end
	end
	for my = 0, dim_y do
		turtle.down()
	end
	turtle.turnRight()
    turtle.forward()
end
